    <Descriptive_Notes>
      <Descriptive_Note>
        <Note_Text>Wood of the Centrolobium genus, ranging in color from yellowish brown to purplish pink, with streaks of red or black. It usually has a straight grain, fine texture, and polishes to a high luster. Balaustre has been used in shipbuilding and as a veneer for cabinetry.</Note_Text>
        <Note_Language>English</Note_Language>
